{
  "texts": [
    "Neighboring agents can also emerge during learning instead of being predetermined, as proposed in GA-Comm [82], MAGIC [91] and FlowComm [92], which explicitly learn a graph structure among agents.",
    "Specifically, in GA-Comm [82] and MAGIC [91], a central unit (e.g., GNN) learns a graph inside and coordinates messages based on the (complete) graph simultaneously.",
    "In this case, agents do not communicate with each other directly; instead, they communicate through a virtual agent who does not affect the environment.",
    "Therefore, we categorize these two works into the proxy category.• Other (Learning) Agents.",
    "If nearby agents are not identified, the set of communicatees typically consists of other (learning) agents."
  ]
}